================================================================================
CONFIGURATION CHANGES ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Modified File: home/gig/common/optional/bspwm.nix
Scope: Polybar module display formatting improvements

ENHANCEMENT CATEGORIES:

1. DATE/TIME FORMAT MODERNIZATION
   - Date format: "%Y-%m-%d" → "%m/%d/%Y" (ISO → US standard)
   - Time format: "%H:%M" → "%I:%M %p" (24-hour → 12-hour with AM/PM)
   - Rationale: Improved accessibility for US-standard time formats

2. SYSTEM MONITORING LABEL STANDARDIZATION
   - CPU module: " " → " CPU " (added descriptive prefix)
   - Memory module: " " → " RAM " (added descriptive prefix)
   - Disk module: " %percentage_used%%" → " DISK %percentage_used%%"
   - Purpose: Enhanced visual clarity and immediate component identification

3. AUDIO INTERFACE IMPROVEMENTS
   - Volume display: " %percentage%%" → " VOL %percentage%%"
   - Mute indicator: " muted" → " MUTED" (capitalized for visibility)
   - Enhancement: Clearer audio status recognition

4. NETWORK CONNECTIVITY ENHANCEMENTS
   - Wireless: Added "WIFI" prefix to connected format
   - Wireless disconnect: Empty string → " WIFI OFF" (explicit status)
   - Ethernet: " " → " ETH " (added descriptive prefix)
   - Ethernet disconnect: Empty string → " ETH OFF" (explicit status)
   - Improvement: Clear network status at all times

5. BATTERY STATUS CLARIFICATION
   - Charging format: Added "BAT" prefix for clarity
   - Discharging format: Added "BAT" prefix for clarity
   - Full battery: " " → " BAT " (consistent labeling)
   - Benefit: Unified battery status presentation

